WHO   — FAXANADU — the World-Tree action-RPG game-world
WHAT  — Faxanadu — Hudson Soft's NES action-RPG inside a dying World Tree: a wandering swordsman returns to ruined Eolis, awakens three poisoned springs, and ascends the branches — Golds, Ranks, Mantras, card-keys, and Jun Chikuma's celebrated score.
WHERE — a dying World Tree the hero climbs from the ruined town of Eolis, to awaken three springs and destroy the Evil One  Framework inputs: Faxanadu; the World Tree; Eolis; the Evil One; King Grieve; the Mantras; the card-keys; Golds & Ranks; Xanadu; Jun Chikuma  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Universe David 0)
WHY   — An action-RPG set inside a giant tree: earn Golds and Ranks, buy weapons, armor and magic, gather the five card-keys, save by Mantras, and climb the branches past the mutated Dwarves to the Evil One.
HOW   — Crystallized from Faxanadu (Hudson Soft, NES 1989) — the Western release of the 1987 Famicom action-RPG, built on Nihon Falcom's licensed Xanadu name.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Return to a ruined town, take up the sword, and climb the dying tree of the world — spring by spring — to the thing the meteor brought.

